The topics addressed in the class were very interesting, but they were presented in an incoherent way. The 'thesis' of each lecture was unclear and it felt more like a slideshow of buildings and historical information rather than the formulation of an argument. The tests and exam had a different format each time. No textbook; you must do readings!
She's super smart and knowledgeable. Also cares deeply about her students.

Her lectures are the longest 2 hours of my life. Her tone is so monotonous it's not only difficult to stay awake in class, it's even harder to take notes.
